    "created_at": "2023-09-14T19:37:36Z",
    "updated_at": "2023-09-14T19:37:36Z",
    "body": "The signing and distribution were failing outright for two reasons:\r\n\r\n1. My Apple password was affected by the LastPass breaches in 2022, so I reset my Apple account password. I forgot that the CI requires an application-specific password on the Apple Developer account, so the CI was unable to authenticate to Apple for signing.\r\n2. Even once I fixed that, it turns out that Apple introduced a separate agreement for paid apps, and I had to accept that to be able to use the notarization services, even though I have no intention of ever developing paid apps.\r\n\r\nI've accepted the relevant agreements and chucked a new app-specific password into GitHub, so hopefully these two issues are solved.\r\n\r\nAs for the version, I think what happened is that a bug in the notarization script didn't suppress error correctly, so we saw a bunch of errors stuffed into the version field in the resulting xml. We switched to release-please since I wrote the initial notarization PR which lets us just pull the version directly out of the tag. I'm opening #5443 which will hopefully fix this issue, but I'm not marking it as something that will close this, since we need to kick off a release to actually test the thing.",
